initCoreRow(25.10)                                          initCoreRow(25.10)

Name
       initCoreRow  - Regenerates rows for the core area and the power domains
       in a design

Syntax
       initCoreRow

       [-help]

       [-powerDomain <string>]

       Regenerates rows for the core area and the power domains in  a  design.
       The  rows  are based on the current row parameters instead of using the
       floorPlan command. You can use this command after importing the design.

       Note: In a common flow, Innovus goes over all technical sites  used  in
       the  netlist  and creates rows for these sites. It chooses the shortest
       tech site in the design (with the smallest height and width) as the de-
       fault-technical-site. All other used tech-sites  with  integer-multiple
       height/width are considered as compatible.

       Note: The initCoreRow command honors the new LEF syntax by default.  It
       supports  the  creation  of rows for sites with offset value defined in
       the LEF file with SITECOREOFFSET (for VERSION 5.8)  and  COREOFFSET(for
       VERSION  6.0).  The  offset  value  is the spacing from the bottom core
       boundary to the location that start to create rows for the site.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the initCoreRow  command.  For  a
              detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man initCoreRow

       -powerDomain <string>
              Specifies the power domain for which rows are to be created.

              Data_type: string, optional

Related Information
              * floorPlan

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

